item.title: Rebecca Black Talks "Friday", Haters & Justin Bieber On 'Good Morning America'
item.description:
Rebecca Black Talks "Friday", Haters & Justin Bieber On 'Good Morning America'
http://Facebook.com/ClevverTV - Become a Fan! http://Twitter.com/ClevverTV - Follow Us! Rebecca Black is finally responding to her YouTube success. Will Justin Bieber hit the stage with her? ClevverTV has your break down right now! Hello friends! I'm Joslyn Davis for ClevverTV in Hollywood where we finally have a Rebecca Black update. And I say finally because our entire crew has become completely obsessed with Rebecca -- who she is, what her story is and how she came to make to the most-talked-about video to hit the internet in quite a long time. And since it is Friday, we thought it would be fun fun fun to bring you the latest on the 8th grader who finally spoke out today on Good Morning America. Sadly, Rebecca has come under attack as a result of her video, as complete strangers are making her the target are very intense cyber bullying. When we posted our first ClevverTV story on the Friday video, even we have to admit, we weren't sure if this was a real video or some sort of parody. Now, we are finally hearing from the tween singer herself, who spoke out about the horrible things people have been saying about her online. Rebecca talked about some of the comments, even admitting that they did make her cry, but now she has a better outlook on the situation -- she also was willing to sing a few lines of the National Anthem -- and you know what guys, she sounded pretty good. So who would her dream collaboration be? Well guys, even Rebecca has Bieber fever. She says she is in love with Justin Bieber. You have to give this girl serious props -- she straight up asked Justin Bieber on television if he would duet with her. Even if you're not as obsessed with her song as we are, you have to admit that she's brave and positive. So what do you guys think are the chances of the Biebs duetting with Rebecca Black? Give us your thoughts right here! For updates on Rebecca Black, stick with ClevverTV all the time by following @ClevverTV on twitter. I'm Joslyn Davis, thanks for watching.
